<TITLE> Ex-presidential candidate disappears in Mexico </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 MEXICO CITY May 16 (bdnews24.com/AFP)  A former presidential candidate has disappeared in Mexico, prompting authorities to launch an investigation into a possible kidnapping, officials said. The probe into the disappearance of Diego Fernandez de Cevallos, who ran for president in 1994 for the National Action Party, was launched on Saturday after his family reported him missing in the city of Queretaro. A pick-up truck belonging to Fernandez de Cevallos, 69, was found at his ranch in Queretaro "with signs of violence," the prosecutor's office reported. However, officials said they did not have any other evidence that would confirm that a kidnapping had indeed taken place. More than 22,700 people have died in spiralling drug violence in Mexico since President Felipe Calderon launched a military crackdown on organized crime, according to official figu
